node.text: Affirmation of the Day: As I lean further and further into an empowering self-narrative, It is important for me to reevaluate the proximity and quality of the people I allow into my life. I allow myself to feel what I need to and to heal at my own pace. I release all chains that block my growth and freedom. I know who I am and I know my value. Anything and anyone that doesn’t align with it, well, they can find the exit. 🧡

node.text:
We are joining @impact to raise funds to support abortion rights. Your donation will support The American Civil Liberties Union. @aclu_nationwide works to fight government abuse and defend individual freedoms including a woman’s right to choose.

Donate to this fundraiser to help the ACLU fight Texas’ unconstitutional abortion ban law and defend abortion rights nationwide.

With your support, the ACLU will keep working to stop extreme abortion bans. If you’re not able to support monetarily, please share this post with your friends and onto your story.

Every donation counts.

➡️ Learn more about The American Civil Liberties Union (@aclu_nationwide) through our fundraiser or visit aclu.orgn

node.text:
“For everyone looking to support women in Texas—whose reproductive rights and access to healthcare have been severely and unjustly limited by the state’s new Senate Bill 8—please see the below resources and organizations.⁣
⁣
- Donate to @avowtexas, a Texas-based group that is helping provide abortion care and information. ⁣
⁣
- Learn more about @fundtexaschoice, which serves pregnant people.⁣
⁣
- Visit and donate to @lilithfund, a nonprofit community providing resources for people who are in need of abortions in the Texas area.⁣
⁣
- @TeaFund is providing Texans seeking abortion care access to financial funds and emotional support. ⁣
⁣
- Support and learn the latest information about the law via @plannedparenthood. They are currently petitioning the law and you can add your name to the petition as well.⁣
⁣
- @theafiyacenter is helping Black women and girls by fighting for reproductive justice.⁣
⁣
- Join a @womensmarch group in your state—they march in every state on October 2 to fight back against #Sb8.⁣
⁣
- Visit needabortion.org for more resources and ways to help fight for women’s reproductive rights, in whatever way you can.” 🧡

node.text:
“You may not be able to predict how to prepare for the future, but you can do this: you can remember moments in the past where you surprised yourself. Moments where you were able to rise up to the challenge even when you did not feel like you were equipped. Moments where you finally managed to climb that mountain after years of doubting yourself.

You have already encountered unknowns before. And you have also already encountered grace. Grace that gives you room to pace yourself with courage and resilience, no matter what remains unknown.” 🧡

“Whenever you start to doubt your strength again, remember what this journey looked like when you first began. You did not know it all, you did not feel strong, but you kept on believing yourself through it all. It was hard to keep going at time but breath by breath, step by step, you have come this far. Even if right now life is still full of uncertainty and stress, know that it is okay, in your own time you will overcome them.” 🧡
